  "elapsed_s": 58.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, as a matter of fact, at one point, we had a fairly high-ranking German officer who was in civilian clothes who stayed and enjoyed very much that Mother was even providing dinner if he was interested in.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was a tenant there for a couple of weeks with us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Unfortunately, no, no, no, but it was a kind of a strange, funny situation.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But that was part of surviving and-- and having-- meeting our daily needs for food.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How did they affect my life?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "With fear-- with fear, with humiliation, with-- with hope that war and that-- that the defeat of these ideologies will come soon, and always question in my mind that what's wrong with us, why people hate us.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I could never understand that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "To me, I thought that Judeo-Christian [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] teachings and heritage should be something which-- which tolerance would be part of the teaching, and that you were the first one who-- who understood what it means to believe in one god and only God and not being adulterer-- idols and not believing in the whole kind of idols of different gods and that we gave the world the first religion which believes in one god, that it should be-- the Jews should be looked on as-- as part of world history and a small nation who survived all this in history with all kind of persecutions.",
      "word_count": 108
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we still were part of it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were back to the original teaching.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I-- I-- I could never understand it, why we were selected to be hated and killed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the anti-Jewish laws then moved us from our homes.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
